Dean S. RESLER v. UNITED STATES of America (two cases). Nos. 3486, 3487. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit April 14, 1947. Raymond M. Sandhouse and Francis L. Shallenberger, both of Sterling, Colo., for appellant. Thomas J. Morrissey, U. S. Atty., and Bart W. O’Hara, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS ancj HUXMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
